# Corp Web Design Alignment (TMaaS)

Marketing pages (`/`, `/marketplace`, `/service/:id`) share the **DQ corp web design system** from `DQ_CORPWEB_PROTOTYPE`. They must **not** mirror the corp homepage section stack or copy patterns.

## Copy punctuation
- Do not use em dashes (`—`) in user-facing copy, meta tags, or email templates. Use commas, colons, periods, or a regular hyphen (`-`) instead.

## Share with corp web (design system)
- Body font: **Plus Jakarta Sans** (`font-sans`), not Inter
- Brand colors: `text-dq-navy` (#030F35), `text-dq-orange` (#FB5535)
- Headings: `font-semibold`, not `font-bold`; hero up to `lg:text-8xl`
- Eyebrow labels: `font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-dq-orange`
- Section padding: `py-24 px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-10`
- Content max-width: `max-w-[1200px] mx-auto` (heroes may use `max-w-7xl`)
- Alternate backgrounds: `white` / `bg-gray-50`
- Navbar: static `sticky top-0 h-16`, no scroll-morph pill effect
- Cards: `rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-dq-orange hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300`
- CTAs: `rounded-full`; primary orange on product landing (`bg-dq-orange`); secondary glass (`bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border`)
- Hero backgrounds: `MeshSection` with `hero-grid` overlay and mesh CSS vars from `index.css`
- Footer section labels: `font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gray-400`
- Footer link columns: **Explore** (Marketplace, Contact Us, internal, flag-gated), **DQ** (Explore DigitalQatalyst, About, external corp web), **Follow Us** (LinkedIn, X, YouTube)
- Footer bottom bar always shows Privacy and Terms linking to `https://www.digitalqatalyst.com/privacy` and `/terms` (external, new tab)
- Corp web links use `https://www.digitalqatalyst.com` base URL; TMaaS product link label is **Marketplace** (not "Design & Deploy Services")
- Platform display name is **Transformation as a Service** (`PLATFORM_NAME` in `src/lib/brandLinks.ts`); acronym is `TMaaS` (`PLATFORM_ACRONYM`); formal line is `TMaaS (Transformation as a Service)` (`PLATFORM_BRAND_LINE`). Do not use "Transformation Management as a Service", "Transformation Marketplace", or "Technology Management as a Service" as the platform name.

## Differentiate for product pages (TMaaS landing)
- Use **product landing IA** per `specs/landing-page-prototype-shell.md` v2, default at `/` (`IndexProductLanding`, `src/components/site/landing/v2/`)
- v1 corp-mirror alternate landing at `/landing-v1` (`IndexTraditional`); `/landing-v2` redirects to `/`
- Hero: TMaaS logo, product badge row, marketplace mockup; orange primary CTA → `/marketplace`
- One dark mesh narrative section (`Why TMaaS`); do not alternate dark sections like corp homepage
- Do **not** add corp-only sections: Team, FAQ, Framework, full ecosystem product grid
- Do **not** copy corp homepage stats, problem copy, or section order verbatim
- Parent brand: optional `Part of DigitalQatalyst` external link; full corp credibility stays on corp web

## Service detail, tab first-heading alignment
Overview, What You Receive, and How It Works first `sectionHeading` share the same top offset: `serviceDetailSplitLead` on split-grid lead columns; `serviceDetailTabLead` on How It Works first `ServiceDetailSection`.

## Service detail, hero mesh (`ServiceDetail.tsx`)
- Scope `heroLight` mesh to the **hero block only** (`absolute inset-0` inside the hero wrapper), never a fixed `h-[520px]` overlay across tabs
- Tabs and related services sit in a sibling `bg-background` section below the hero

## Service detail, About This Service (Overview tab)
Match the approved two-column mockup in `ServiceDetailAboutSection.tsx`:
- Grid: `serviceDetailSplitGrid` + `serviceDetailSplitLead`, **top-aligned** (`items-start` only); lead column `md:pt-7` aligns `sectionHeading` with side-card title; card title before icon
- Left: `sectionHeading` from `brandAccent.ts` (`text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-dq-navy`); two paragraphs at `text-base leading-[1.7] text-[#667085]` with `mt-6 space-y-5`
- Right “Who it’s for” card: `rounded-2xl p-7 md:p-8`, experience collection uses `bg-[#F3F4F9]` (not strong `violet-50`); white circular icon well; collection accent icon colour via `getAudienceCardAccent`
- Copy: P1 narrative intro (not raw `description` themes shorthand); P2 from `OVERVIEW_CLOSING_BY_TYPE`; audience without solution-name injection for experience advisory
- Do not use `lg:` breakpoint for this grid, two columns from `md:` upward

## Service detail, section headings
All in-page section `h2` titles (About, Key Outcomes, Related Services, tab panels via `ServiceDetailSection`) use **`sectionHeading`** from `@/lib/brandAccent`, corp web card title scale (`text-xl font-semibold`), not `text-2xl`/`font-bold` or responsive `md:text-3xl` jumps.

## Service detail, What You Receive tab
Match `ServiceDetailWhatYouReceiveTab.tsx` (same top-row pattern as Overview / About):
- Top row: same split-grid tokens as Overview, **Deliverables Summary** + **At a glance** card (duration, scope only)
- **Deliverables Breakdown**: sole enumerated deliverables list with descriptions (`getDeliverableBreakdown`)
- **Modules & Applications**: deploy accordion below; `sectionHeading` (no eyebrow)
- Deliverable titles from existing `deliverables` prop only

## Service detail, Key Outcomes (Overview tab)
Match the approved four-column mockup in `ServiceDetailKeyOutcomesSection.tsx`:
- Horizontal row of four equal columns on `lg:` with thin `border-gray-200` vertical dividers (not bordered cards); **symmetric** `px-8` gutter on every column (never asymmetric `pr` on first / `pl` on rest)
- Orange step numbers `01`–`04` (`text-4xl font-bold text-dq-orange`), then `font-medium` navy outcome title (lighter than `sectionHeading`), then `#667085` description
- Keep titles/descriptions from `getKeyOutcomes()`, layout only, do not swap in mockup copy

## Service detail, Why It Matters tab
Match `ServiceDetailWhyItMattersTab.tsx` + `whyItMattersContent.ts`:
- Intro: `sectionHeading` “Why This Service Matters”; hook line `font-medium text-dq-navy`; problem paragraph `#667085`
- Before / After: single `rounded-2xl` comparison container (`shadow-card`); `lg:grid-cols-2` panels with gradient backgrounds (gray-50 → white / orange-50 → white)
- Panel badges: pill chips, gray for Before, orange-tinted for After; stacked item cards with icon wells + `01`–`03` mono labels (not a 3-col grid inside each half)
- Centre transition: orange `ArrowRight` circle on `lg+`; mobile divider row with arrow between panels
- Copy from `getWhyItMattersContent(service)`, contextualise by `collection`, `serviceType`, and solution name; exact override for `online web presence|advisory`

## Do Not
- Reintroduce morphing navbar or Inter as default body font
- Reskin corp homepage section-for-section with product copy swaps
- Use `rounded-xl` + `border-navy-100` for marketing cards when corp web pattern applies
- Change page logic/routing when doing styling-only alignment work
